content:
ChatGPT is surprisingly bad a poetry.

I'd have thought composing a poem when given a theme and structure woukd be well within it's actual capabilities, bit even after I really broke down how to write a sonnet, with line counts, rhyme schemes and had low expectations for quality it couldn't get even remotely close.

I'd even ask it afterwards: how many lines does a sonnet have, it knew the answer was 14, but it just would not stop at 14 lines when writing, and would ignore my rhyme schemes while gaslighting me about it.

I know LLMs are woefully bad bullshit engines, but I thought it would at least be able to have a crack at a high school english assignment I've seen otherwise quite incapable students at least get the basics right for.
